OL,5,Cafford
OL,7,FAnyone who feels otherwise needs to
OL,8,Fsay where the money would come from.
OL,10,FShould other BBC services or
OL,11,Fprogrammes face the chop instead?
OL,13,FIt's easy to argue that certain
OL,14,Fpopular TV programmes or Radio 1 and
OL,15,F2 do not deserve public money while
OL,16,Fthe market alone would never provide
OL,17,FNewsnight or English local radio. But
OL,18,Fhuge numbers of people enjoy these
OL,19,Fprogrammes and services.
